---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { BOOKING_URL } from '../consts';

const seoServiceSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Service',
  name: 'Local SEO Strategy',
  provider: {
    '@type': 'LocalBusiness',
    name: 'Granite State Tech Services',
    url: 'https://granitestatetechservices.com'
  },
  areaServed: {
    '@type': 'State',
    name: 'New Hampshire'
  },
  serviceType: 'Local SEO audit and strategy',
  url: 'https://granitestatetechservices.com/seo',
  offers: {
    '@type': 'Offer',
    availability: 'https://schema.org/InStock',
    priceCurrency: 'USD'
  }
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Local SEO for NH Service Businesses | Granite State Tech Services"
  description="Local SEO that fills your calendar, not just your dashboard. Technical fixes, service pages that rank, and content that brings in the right leads."
  structuredData={seoServiceSchema}
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Local SEO for New Hampshire</p>
    <h1>Local SEO that fills your calendar,<br>not your dashboard.</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      Most SEO agencies hand you a PDF of rankings. We focus on the searches that turn into
      phone calls — then make sure your site closes them.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href={BOOKING_URL}>Request a free SEO audit</a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#how-it-works">See how it works</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="problem surface">
    <h2>You've probably been here before.</h2>
    <p>
      You paid for SEO. You got a monthly report full of graphs going up and to the right.
      Traffic increased. Rankings improved.
    </p>
    <p>
      But when you checked your calendar? Same as before.
    </p>
    <p>
      That's because most SEO work chases volume. More keywords, more blog posts, more backlinks.
      None of it matters if the people finding you aren't looking to hire someone in New Hampshire
      this week.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="how-it-works">
    <h2>We start with the searches that book calls.</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">
      Not all keywords are equal. "Best HVAC company Manchester NH" is worth 100x more than
      "how does a furnace work." We build your SEO around the searches people make right before
      they pick up the phone.
    </p>

    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Step 01</p>
        <h3>Fix the foundation</h3>
        <p>
          Technical issues that keep you from ranking — slow pages, broken links, missing schema,
          messy Google Business Profile. We clean it up in the first two weeks.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Step 02</p>
        <h3>Build pages that convert</h3>
        <p>
          One focused service page for each thing you do, written for the people searching for it.
          Clear CTAs. Location targeting. Answers to the questions your prospects actually ask.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Step 03</p>
        <h3>Create content that compounds</h3>
        <p>
          Strategic blog posts that rank for long-tail searches and funnel readers toward your
          service pages. Every article ties back to a booking path.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">What you get</p>
      <h2>Clear deliverables. Measurable progress.</h2>
      <p>
        Every engagement comes with concrete outputs you can see and measure — not just a
        monthly report you'll never read.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="surface deliverables-panel">
      <ul class="list">
        <li><span>01</span> Technical audit with a prioritized fix list.</li>
        <li><span>02</span> Optimized service pages — one per core offer.</li>
        <li><span>03</span> Google Business Profile cleanup and optimization.</li>
        <li><span>04</span> Content calendar with three months of topics.</li>
        <li><span>05</span> Monthly reporting tied to leads, not just traffic.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pricing">
    <h2>Straightforward pricing.</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">One-time</p>
        <h3>SEO Audit</h3>
        <p class="price">Starts at $500</p>
        <p>
          Complete technical review, competitor scan, and prioritized action plan. Take it to any
          provider or have us execute it.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Ongoing</p>
        <h3>Monthly SEO</h3>
        <p class="price">Starts at $1,200/mo</p>
        <p>
          Technical fixes, content creation, service page optimization, and monthly reporting.
          Three-month minimum so we have time to show results.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <p class="eyebrow">Per page</p>
        <h3>Service Page Build</h3>
        <p class="price">Starts at $400/page</p>
        <p>
          Standalone service pages optimized for local search with conversion-focused copy and
          schema markup.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
    <p class="pricing-note">
      Every engagement starts with a free strategy call where I'll assess your current situation
      and tell you exactly what I'd prioritize.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <h2>Straight answers.</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <details>
        <summary>How long before I see results?</summary>
        <p>
          Technical fixes often improve rankings within 2-4 weeks. Content-driven results take
          2-3 months to compound. I'll set realistic expectations for your specific situation on
          our first call.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>I've done SEO before and it didn't work. Why would this be different?</summary>
        <p>
          Most SEO focuses on traffic volume. We focus on conversion-intent keywords — the
          searches people make when they're ready to hire. Fewer visitors, better visitors.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do I need a new website for this to work?</summary>
        <p>
          Not necessarily. If your current site loads fast and has a clear booking path, we can
          work with it. If it's holding you back, I'll tell you.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What do you actually need from me?</summary>
        <p>
          Access to your Google Business Profile, Google Search Console, and about an hour per
          month for check-ins. We handle the rest.
        </p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can I just get the audit and decide later?</summary>
        <p>
          Yes. The audit stands on its own. No pressure to continue with monthly services.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="final-cta surface">
    <h2>Find out what's holding you back.</h2>
    <p>
      Book a free 30-minute SEO audit call. I'll pull up your site, your competitors, and your
      Google presence live — and show you the three highest-impact fixes you can make this month.
    </p>
    <p class="guarantee">
      No contracts. No pitch deck. Just an honest look at where you stand.
    </p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary btn-xl" href={BOOKING_URL}>Book your free audit call</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .btn-xl {
    padding: 1.2rem 2.4rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .page-hero {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .hero-sub {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  .hero-actions {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .problem {
    padding: var(--space-2xl);
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: var(--space-3xl) auto;
  }

  .problem h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .problem p {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .deliverables-panel {
    padding: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .pricing h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .price {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .pricing-note {
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .faq h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .faq-list {
    max-width: 720px;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  details {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background: var(--surface-strong);
    padding: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  summary {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  summary::after {
    content: '+';
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 200ms var(--ease-out);
  }

  details[open] summary::after {
    content: '\2212';
  }

  summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  details p {
    padding: 0 var(--space-lg) var(--space-lg);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .final-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-3xl);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .final-cta p {
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .guarantee {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
</style>
